article.headline: Wofford 28, The Citadel 7
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. (AP) -- Dane Romero rushed for 50 yards and a touchdown and Kevious Johnson had 12 carries for 81 yards to lift Wofford to a 28-7 victory over The Citadel on Saturday. Romero's 38-yard touchdown run put the Terriers (5-1, 3-0 Southern Conference) ahead for good with 5:06 left in the third quarter. Josh Collier completed 4-of-11 passes for 86 yards and had a 1-yard touchdown run. Michael Hobbs ran for 31 yards and a touchdown while Justice Joslin added eight yards and a score. The Bulldogs (3-2, 1-1 SoCon) threatened twice in the first quarter, driving deep into Wofford territory on their next possession. But the drive was stopped on the Wofford 13 when Duran Lawson's pass intended for Tory Cooper was incomplete. Lawson went 26-of-43 for 222 yards to lead the Bulldogs. Dwight House had a 42-yard interception return to give The Citadel its only score of the night. Andre Roberts caught 12 passes for 123 yards for the Bulldogs. Tory Cooper led The Citadel in rushing with 71 yards on 19 carries.
